This paper deals with influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis and modeling of social networks. The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the Independent Cascade (IC) and Linear Threshold (LT) models, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper deals with time-critical influence maximization, which could place it in cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
